"title": "5704: inheritance, material",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5704",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Family property was normally handed down in biblical times through sons, with a special place for the firstborn.  The land of Israel was regarded as the nation's inheritance.</p>\n<h2>Inheritance of family property</h2>\n<h3>It was normally handed down through sons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:3-Gen15:4\">GEN 15:3–15:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:5\">GEN 25:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:1\">JER 49:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:16-Ezek46:17\">EZK 46:16–46:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:38\">MAT 21:38</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:7\">MRK 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:14\">LUK 20:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:30\">GAL 4:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:10\">GEN 21:10</a></p>\n<h3>The absence of a son as a male heir was seen as a serious disadvantage</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:21\">GEN 25:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:5-Deut25:6\">DEU 25:5–25:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:17\">JDG 21:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:10-1Sam1:11\">1SA 1:10–1:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:4-2Sam14:7\">2SA 14:4–14:7</a></p>\n<h3>Other relatives could inherit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:8-Num27:11\">NUM 27:8–27:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:1-Num27:7\">NUM 27:1–27:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:2-Num36:4\">NUM 36:2–36:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:1-Ruth4:4\">RUT 4:1–4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:15\">JOB 42:15</a></p>\n<h3>Servants could inherit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:2-Gen15:3\">GEN 15:2–15:3</a></p>\n<h3>Inheritance before death</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:11-Luke15:12\">LUK 15:11–15:12</a> <em>The son's asking for his inheritance is perhaps to be seen as an insult.</em></p>\n<h3>The rights of the firstborn</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:15-Deut21:17\">DEU 21:15–21:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:19\">GEN 27:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:32\">GEN 27:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr21:3\">2CH 21:3</a></p>\n<h2>Stewardship of one's own inheritance</h2>\n<h3>It must be preserved</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:2-1Kgs21:3\">1KI 21:2–21:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:22\">PRO 13:22</a></p>\n<h3>It must not be squandered</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:16\">HEB 12:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:29-Gen25:34\">GEN 25:29–25:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:13\">LUK 15:13</a></p>\n<h3>It must not be fought over</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:13-Luke12:15\">LUK 12:13–12:15</a></p>\n<h2>Respect for the inheritance of others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:2-Mic2:3\">MIC 2:2–2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:18\">EZK 46:18</a></p>\n<h2>The land as Israel's inheritance</h2>\n<h3>It was promised to Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:6-Gen12:7\">GEN 12:6–12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:14-Gen13:15\">GEN 13:14–13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:7\">GEN 15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:18-Gen15:21\">GEN 15:18–15:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:8\">GEN 17:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:3-Acts7:5\">ACT 7:3–7:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8\">HEB 11:8</a></p>\n<h3>It was confirmed to Moses and the patriarchs</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:2-Exod6:4\">EXO 6:2–6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:8\">EXO 6:8</a></p>\n<h3>Entry was denied because of sin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:22-Num14:23\">NUM 14:22–14:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:21\">DEU 4:21</a></p>\n<h3>It was entered by faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8-Heb11:9\">HEB 11:8–11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:30\">HEB 11:30</a></p>\n<h3>It was conquered by Joshua</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:1-Josh1:4\">JOS 1:1–1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:23\">JOS 11:23</a></p>\n<h3>It was allotted to the tribes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:1-Josh14:5\">JOS 14:1–14:5</a></p>\n<h3>It was a land for the godly</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:9\">PSA 37:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:11\">PSA 37:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:22\">PSA 37:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:29\">PSA 37:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:34\">PSA 37:34</a></p>\n<h3>It was a good inheritance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:8\">EXO 3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:24\">LEV 20:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:21-Num13:27\">NUM 13:21–13:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:7-Deut8:8\">DEU 8:7–8:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:10-Deut11:12\">DEU 11:10–11:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:9-Ps65:10\">PSA 65:9–65:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:7\">JER 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>The LORD's inheritance in the land</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:17\">EXO 15:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:19\">JOS 22:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:12\">ZEC 2:12</a></p>\n<h3>The inheritance was lost through sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:4\">JER 17:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:1\">PSA 79:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:2\">LAM 5:2</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment on the nations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:14-Jer12:17\">JER 12:14–12:17</a></p>\n<h3>The land was regained through grace</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra1:1-Ezra1:2\">EZR 1:1–1:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:10-Jer29:11\">JER 29:10–29:11</a></p>\n<h3>God renewed his promises</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:34-Ps69:36\">PSA 69:34–69:36</a></strong> <em>The Jews did return to the land; some look, however, for a further fulfilment of these promises in the future; others see them as fulfilled in Jesus Christ.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:13\">ISA 57:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:13-Isa58:14\">ISA 58:13–58:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:7\">ISA 61:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:9\">ISA 65:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:12\">ZEC 8:12</a></p>",
